decks.notes: This deck focuses on using cards like Thoughtseize and Force of Will to disrupt the opponent's game plan while generating card advantage with Ancestral Recall and Treasure Cruise. It aims to control the board through removal spells like Fatal Push and Dismember, while utilizing its graveyard with cards like Insatiable Avarice and Dark Ritual. The deck also has a strong late game with powerful threats like Dauthi Voidwalker and Snapcaster Mage. Overall, the deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver the opponent through efficient control and card advantage strategies.

The deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with Dredge creatures like Golgari Grave-Troll, Stinkweed Imp, and Golgari Thug using cards like Bazaar of Baghdad and Serum Powder. By discarding cards and using graveyard interactions, the deck aims to create a powerful board presence with cards like Ichorid, Narcomoeba, and Prized Amalgam. It also utilizes spells like Force of Will and Force of Negation to protect its combo pieces. Creeping Chill provides additional reach and damage, while Hollow One and Silversmote Ghoul offer additional threats and recursion options.

The deck focuses on using Underworld Breach to combo off and win the game quickly, utilizing powerful cards like Black Lotus, Bolas's Citadel, and Lórien Revealed. It aims to cast multiple spells from the graveyard in a single turn, generating a large amount of mana with cards like Tolarian Academy and Moxen. The deck also includes disruption with cards like Force of Will and Hullbreacher to protect the combo and stop opponent's strategies. The goal is to assemble the combo pieces quickly and efficiently to overwhelm the opponent and win the game.

The focus of this deck is to control the game by utilizing powerful spells and creatures to disrupt the opponent's strategy while maintaining card advantage and tempo. The deck includes various counterspells, removal spells, and card draw effects to outplay the opponent and maintain control of the game. With the use of strong control elements and efficient mana base, this deck aims to dominate the battlefield and dictate the pace of the game.

This deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan by playing hatebears such as Archon of Emeria and Chancellor of the Annex while applying pressure with aggressive creatures like Witch Enchanter and Seasoned Dungeoneer. It also utilizes powerful mana acceleration to quickly deploy threats and lock down the opponent with cards like Wasteland, Chalice of the Void, and Trinisphere. The combination of disruptive elements and aggressive creatures makes it difficult for the opponent to execute their strategy effectively, giving this deck a strong advantage in the early game.

The deck focuses on using hatebears to disrupt opponents while also applying aggressive pressure. It aims to limit opponent's resources with cards like Wasteland, Containment Priest, and Archon of Emeria, while also utilizing fast mana with Moxen and ramping with Ancient Tomb. The deck looks to lock opponents out of the game by combining disruptive creatures with hate cards like Chalice of the Void and Trinisphere. It aims to control the game tempo and disrupt opponent's game plan while establishing a board presence with the aggressive hatebears.
